subSections.title: Usage notes
subSections.text: In Mainland China's ''Modern Chinese General Chinese Characters Stroke Order Standard'' ({{w2|zh|现代汉语通用字笔顺规范}}) and ''{{w|Xiandai Hanyu Guifan Cidian}}'' ({{w2|zh|pref=《|现代汉语规范词典|suf=》}}), the third stroke touches the first stroke ({{zh-l|相接}}) but does not cross over it. In the Taiwan, Japan and Hong Kong standards, the third stroke crosses over the first stroke ({{zh-l|相交}}).
